 in the core of two\ngalaxies is indicative of in-situ star formation. We conclude that the NSCs in\nthese dwarf galaxies likely originated as globular clusters that migrated to\nthe core of the galaxy which have built up their mass mainly through mergers\nwith other infalling clusters, with gas-inflow leading to in-situ star\nformation playing a secondary role.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 May 2020 14:44:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
